to the editor the answer to the very real problem you describe heft of students backpacks turns into textbook battle front page dec 24 is not legislation to lighten textbooks or issuing each student two sets of books rather classrooms need to be stocked with class sets one book for each pupil of the textbooks that students use in those rooms i will never forget the day that i delivered a class set of textbooks to a ninth grade global history class the class rose to a standing ovation that simple act removed about five pounds from each student 's overstuffed backpack if a school can not afford to do that then simply place an extra set or half set of books on a cart that can be rolled from room to room throughout the day this will allow students to leave their weighty and expensive textbooks at home tony scarnati whitestone queens dec 24 2002

